<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kebich Urges Strengthening Ties With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012210293 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1459 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3012210293 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Belinform-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 30 Dec -- Belarusian Prime Minister 
Vyacheslav Kebich said today that "interaction with Russia is 
the cornerstone of the republic's policy." 
  "We firmly believe that people need to follow our course 
toward an economic union within the CIS framework, a single 
ruble zone with Russia, and coordinated customs space as an 
opportunity and necessity to live and work in a civilized way," 
he said today at a reception for diplomats accredited in Minsk. 
  The premier said: The basis of our foreign policy is giving 
up force and a threat of force and giving up nuclear weapons. 
"We were the first among the former USSR republics and among the 
world's states in general, who, without putting forward any 
preliminary conditions to the world community, began nuclear 
disarmament. By doing this, we laid our own little brick in the 
common foundation for European and international security. At 
the same time, we are not expecting any gratitude from the world 
community. The main thing for us is trust, mutual 
understanding, and an opportunity for full-blooded international 
cooperation," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

