<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Shushkevich Delivers New Year's Address </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112201893 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1730 GMT 
31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112201893 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [New Year's message by President Stanislav </F>
Shushkevich--recorded] 
  [Text] Esteemed citizens of the Commonwealth of 
Independent States! My passionate desire is that under no 
circumstances do we ever discard the better things we had in the 
past. It seems to me that we have all the preconditions to use 
them, to regenerate and strengthen them on a new and fundamental 
basis. We are able to cooperate in a worthy fashion; each 
nation can take care of itself. But it would be senseless in 
some ways if there were no cooperation. I would say this: The 
great community we had before must not be lost under any 
circumstances. A worthy, legal basis of cooperation must be 
created, and this is being done within the framework of the CIS. 
The Commonwealth must be established as conceived at Viskuli 
[the Viskuli agreement which was reached at Belovezhskaya 
Pushcha and named after the government residence in Brest oblast 
where talks took place] as cooperation of the cultures, the 
peoples, and the economies. One must say that our mutual 
relations must not be guided by rulers or ideological dogma. We 
must join together in that popular upsurge of friendship which 
always existed. 
  On behalf of the Republic of Belarus, the leadership of the 
Republic of Belarus, and the people of the Republic of Belarus, 
I would like to wish you a happy New Year, would like 1993 to be 
the last difficult year of reform for you, and hope that in 1994 
we achieve what we are striving for, that each person can be 
master of his own fate. We are not alone in the process of 
transforming totalitarian structures into democratic ones, and 
if China and the Baltic countries can manage a good showing in 
the development of industry and the economy, I would like this 
to be achieved by all CIS countries. We have sufficient 
intellectual potential and enough patience for this, and I am 
convinced that 1994 will bring us new successes. I wish you a 
happy New Year, a happy 1994 and the years after it! I wish you 
happiness and joy and all the best that life offers! 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

