<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Snegur Delivers New Year's Address </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112171993 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1600 GMT 
31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112171993 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [New Year's address by President Mirca Snegur "to Mayak </F>
listeners" -- recorded] 
  [Text] The Republic of Moldova ends 1993 on an optimistic 
note. We have had a peaceful year. We have gathered a good food 
harvest. We have moved forward along the path of economic 
reforms. It is sufficient to say that privatization has begun. 
A national currency -- the Moldovan lei -- has been introduced. 
I think that these are good grounds for optimism and a good 
starting point for the new year, 1994, on which we are placing 
great hopes. Especially because recently the meeting of heads 
of CIS states agreed on new ways toward economic integration and 
the creation of conditions for the normal functioning of the 
national economies. 
  On behalf of the people of Moldova, I congratulate all the 
people of the world from my heart on the new year of 1994. I 
wish you all strong health, great happiness, peace, and 
prosperity. 
  Happy New Year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

