<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Snegur Reviews 1993 With Diplomatic Corps Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112122393 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1113 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3112122393 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to President Mircea Snegur, 1993 has been 
not easy for Moldova. 
  Receiving members of the diplomatic corps, accredited to 
Moldova, in Chisinau on Thursday night for a New Year he 
mentioned among the country's main problems the unresolved 
issues on Transdniestria and Gagauzia (southern Moldova), the 
shortage of goods, growing prices, and falling population 
incomes. 
  However, these setbacks, in his opinion, are compensated by 
obvious rewards, including the passage of democratic laws, the 
introduction of a national currency, and the population's 
growing confidence in irreversible reforms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

