<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Almaty Radio Reports Address </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0101102094 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0700 GMT 
1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0101102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kazakh </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Nursultan Nazarbayev addressed the peoples 
of Kazakhstan with a New Year's message. He said: Despite the 
difficulties of the present period we managed to preserve our 
republic' main asset -- public and political stability, civil 
and interethnic accord. This is the cornerstone on the basis of 
which we succeeded in avoiding economic and political upheavals 
and we can confidently face the future. Maintaining such an 
atmosphere is most valuable and we can be proud of this. It 
could facilitate the process of reforms in our society. 
  I am grateful to you, my compatriots and like-minded people, 
for your support. By the powers, that have been given to me by 
the Constitution and you, I guarantee observation of the 
principle of equality and liberties of all people, irrespective 
of nationality, religion, and social status. Kazakhstanis 
should not worry about their future and the future of their 
children. All of us have a common motherland, the Republic of 
Kazakhstan, and we should think about its prosperity. The 
current year should become one of the more important stages on 
this path. I wish optimism, wisdom, and strength to each 
Kazakhstani and each family so as to undergo all the trials with 
credit. Happy New Year, my dear compatriots. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

