<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Welcomes CIS Noninterference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112122793 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1113 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3112122793 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kazakh Foreign Minister Taleutay Suleymenov praised 
the Ashgabat Declaration at a news conference in Almaty Thursday 
[30 December]. 
  He highly appreciated the pledge made by CIS member states 
not to interfere into one another's internal affairs, respect 
one another's territorial integrity, never apply economic 
pressure and fight expansionism, chauvinism and ethnic enmity. 
  Suleymenov also stressed the importance of Ashgabat 
decisions 
on the setting up of a Commonwealth economic union. 
  "We should follow the example set by Western countries," he 
emphasized. In his view, if the CIS economic union is a 
success, a transnational currency may be negotiated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

