<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Holds Talks With Afghanistan on Refugees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012160493 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1344 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012160493 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tajik and Afghan officials met at Sherkhan, a town 
in northern Afghanistan on the border with Tajikistan, on 
Wednesday [29 December]. Taking part in the meeting were Tajik 
Foreign Ministry officials, members of the Parliamentary 
Commission on Tajik Refugees' Repatriation and representatives 
of Afghanistan's National Islamic Movement, led by General 
Abdurashid Dustum. 
  The influential general controls large areas in northern 
Afghanistan on the border with Tajikistan. 
  His envoys are reported to have informed the other side of 
Kabul's readiness to put him in charge of Sherkhan. 
  His emissaries assured their Tajik counterparts that Dustum 
would do all he can to restore a transit camp for Tajik refugees 
at Sherkhan. In their words, Dustum's units will guarantee the 
safe return of Tajik fugitives to their homeland. 
  More than 50,000 Tajiks fled into Afghanistan at the peak of 
military hostilities there in 1992. 

</TEXT>

