<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation `Still Calm' on Afghan Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301110694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 0950 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0301110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation is still calm on the Tajik-Afghan 
border. The Russian troops stationed in Tajikistan informed 
INTERFAX, however, that the calm would be temporary. 
  The military link this with the positive results of Afghan 
President Borhanoddin Rabbani's visit to Tajikistan at the end 
of 1993, with the cold and snowy weather in the mountains and 
with rifts between Afganistan's various political forces. 
  A few days ago, two thirds of the Kazakh battalion operating 
in the territory of the Khorog border-guard unit in accordance 
with last year's Minsk agreement, were removed from Tajik 
territory. However, no replenishments have arrived yet, all of 
which may weaken this section of the Tajik-Afghan border. 

</TEXT>

