<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Chief Says `No Real Threat' of Seizure From Outside </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012192493 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1742 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012192493 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The chairman of the National Security Committee of 
Tajikistan, General Saidamir Zukhurov, has said that there is no 
real threat of Tajikistan's seizure from the outside, since the 
republic has enough forces to rebuff an aggression. 
  In an interview with Interfax Thursday, he said that the so- 
called "Tajik government in exile" does not present any threat 
to the republic's legitimate authorities. However, it will 
trouble the country and destabilize the social and political 
situation. 
  Zukhurov said that the Dushanbe authorities are prepared for 
talks with both the armed and political opposition. "It is up to 
them to have their say," he said. 

</TEXT>

