<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Niyazov's New Year's Message </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112190993 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1734 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112190993 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [New Year's message from President Saparmurad Niyazov in </F>
Ashgabat -- recorded] 
  [Text] Esteemed friends and citizens of our Commonwealth. 
On the eve of the new year I send my best wishes for happiness 
and prosperity to everyone, to every family, to every region, 
and to every country. The end of the outgoing year and the 
results of the Ashgabat meeting of the Commonwealth heads of 
state have brought hope that in the interests of our peoples we 
can cooperate to mutual advantage. 
  The first steps in this direction have been taken. Openness, 
equal partnership, trust and the preservation of economic ties 
will help us overcome the difficulties. 
  As the new year approaches, everyone imagines peace in their 
own way. We in Turkmenistan are concerned not just about our 
own problems, but also about problems that arise for our 
Commonwealth partners. We are happy at every success of theirs. 
Turkmens say that peace and prosperity in the house of your 
neighbor are your peace and prosperity. So on this new year's 
eve, on behalf of the Turkmen people, I wish all of you peace 
and prosperity. 
  Let the new year bring you happiness, joy, and health. A 
happy new year to you! 

</TEXT>

