<H3> <TI>   Government Suspends Publication of Russian Newspapers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012191093 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1742 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012191093 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a surprise move, the Uzbek Government has 
suspended the publication of two Russian newspapers, PRAVDA and 
RABOCHAYA TRIBUNA. No formal explanation has been given. 
  Since the two papers are printed in Tashkent, the decision 
has affected subscribers not only in Uzbekistan but also 
Tajikistan and Kyrgyzstan, and parts of Kazakhstan and 
Turkmenistan. 
  Local observers say RABOCHAYA TRIBUNA may have been punished 
because of its carrying of an article about LDP [Liberal 
Democratic Party] leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy in its December 
24 issue. 

</TEXT>

