<H3> <TI>   Government Decides To Join GATT </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2912212693 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 2000 GMT 29 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2912212693 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lithuanian Government has decided to join the 
General Agreement on Trade and Tariffs [as heard] and to 
regulate the country's foreign trade in conformity with 
internationally accepted principles. Lithuania has acted as an 
observer in the GATT talks since the autumn of 1992. For 
Lithuania, joining GATT means obtaining the most favored nation 
status among the [word indistinct] countries of the world. 
(?Observers) say that by joining GATT, Lithuania would stabilize 
its foreign trade and stimulate the flow of foreign investments 
into Lithuania. 

</TEXT>

