<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3112151793 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3112151793 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense Ministry press service reported that tension 
persists on the Armenian-Azerbaijani border. The defensive 
positions around Dirants in Idzhevanskiy Rayon were shelled from 
Azerbaijani territory at 1320 on 30 December. The enemy fired 
toward Sevkar in the same rayon between 1730-1750. The 
artillery shelling of Dirants resumed in the early hours of 31 
December. The enemy also opened fired on the border post near 
Vahan in Krasnoselskiy Rayon during the daytime on 30 December. 
The defensive positions around Yeraskhavan in Araratskiy Rayon 
were fired upon from Nakhichevan in the evening of 30 December. 
There were no casualties. The Armenian side refrained from 
retaliating. 

</TEXT>

