<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Warns Aliyev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112105393 Yerevan Radio Yerevan in English 2340 GMT 30 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112105393 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Radio Yerevan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 29 December, in the evening, Armenian President 
Levon Ter-Petrosyan had four telephone conversations with the 
president of Azerbaijan, Mr. Heydar Aliyev. The Armenian 
president demanded from his Azeri counterpart to stop the 
bombardment of the Noyemberyan, Idzhevan and Daush districts of 
the Republic of Armenia at once or else the Armenian side will 
similarly respond to the Azeri side. 
  The ARMENPRES news agency, quoting Armenian Defence Ministry 
sources, said that after the telephone conversation of the 
Armenian president with Aliyev the bombardment of the 
northeastern districts of Armenia stopped at once. The 
situation there is reported calm during the night and during the 
day. 

</TEXT>

