<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijan Accused of Preventing Pipeline Repair </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3012201093 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3012201093 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Armenian Government in Yerevan; </F>
date not given] 
  [Text] Armenian Deputy Prime Minister Vigen Chitechyan and 
Armenian State Minister Gagik Shakhbazyan are in Tbilisi for 
talks with Georgian leaders on repairing the bombed gas pipeline 
and improving freight transportation. 
  The Azerbaijani Army used insolent force against the 
representatives of the Armenian leadership, the Georgian 
experts, and the security forces who had gone to repair the gas 
pipeline that was blown up on 24 December in the Azeri-inhabited 
region in Georgia's Marneulinskiy Rayon, north of Armenia. In 
this way, the Azerbaijani Army virtually prevented the start of 
repair work on the gas pipeline. 
  The Armenian Government views this action as a gross 
interference in the internal affairs of a sovereign state. Such 
interference creates tension that is fraught with new and 
unpredictable consequences for the region. 
  The Government of the Armenian Republic hopes that the 
Georgian authorities will take the appropriate measures to 
prevent infringements by the Azerbaijani side and that the 
Azerbaijani leadership will refrain from carrying out acts of 
sabotage in another country that directly affect Armenia's vital 
interests. 

</TEXT>

