<H3> <TI>   Leaders Discuss Transit Cargo Problems </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3012151093 Yerevan SNARK in English 0903 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC3012151093 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, December 29 (SNARK) -- Today the Armenian 
President Levon Ter-Petrosyan has a phone talks with Eduard 
Shevardnadze, the Head of the Georgian state. As SNARK was 
informed at the press-center of the Armenian president, a 
problem of cargo conveyance for Armenia and the restoration of 
gas pipe-line damaged in the Marneul region in Georgia was 
discussed. 
  In the opinion of most observers, transit Armenian cargo's 
plundering has got in Georgia a kind of official character. As 
a result, hundreds of railroad cars and trucks don't get [to] 
their destination places in Armenia. Georgia takes the most 
part of gas from Turkmenistan, for which Armenia has already 
paid in gold. Vazgen Sargisyan, the Armenian state minister, has 
said recently that "the Armenian government has to feed not only 
Armenia but also Georgia." 

</TEXT>

