<H3> <TI>   Armenians Reportedly Attack Azerbaijani Village </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112170493 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1557 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3112170493 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Armenian troops on Friday morning launched an 
offensive on Bash-Gervend, a village about 10-15 km north-east 
of Agdam, Azerbaijan's Defense Ministry said. 
  The Armenians concentrated most of their attacking troops, 
supported by 20 tanks and armored personnel carriers, in the 
area between Agdam and Barda. The Azerbaijani army has put up a 
stiff defense, the ministry said. It said the Armenians, in the 
past 24 hours, had lost three armored vehicles, two cannon and 
one Grad multiple-rocket launcher. 
  Fighting was also raging on Friday around the border between 
Fizuli and Beylagan Districts, where Armenian forces were 
attacking Azerbaijani positions near the Agburun strategic 
height. 

</TEXT>

