<F P=102>  LD3112125693 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1113 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3112125693 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Azeri troops attacked Karabakh positions in the 
north of the Mardakertskiy District Friday, officials in the 
Karabakh army press center told Interfax. They said that the 
Azeris had retreated after losing two tanks and nearly 40 troops. 
  On the day before Karabakh units stood their ground against 
enemy attacks in the north of the Mardakertskiy District and in 
the east of the Martuniskiy District of the Nagorno Karabakh 
Republic. No data on casualties was immediately available. 
  A Karabakh army spokesman said that six Azeri tanks and four 
armored personnel carriers (APC) had been knocked out and five 
tanks captured and repaired in recent days, over 700 Azeri 
soldiers had been killed. The Karabakh forces lost three tanks, 
two APCs and 42 men. 

