<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanctions Against Armenia Urged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3112170293 Baku Radio Baku International Service in Azeri 
1300 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3112170293 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of statement by the Azerbaijan Ministry of Foreign </F>
Affairs; date not given] 
  [Text] Armenia's armed aggression against Azerbaijan 
continues to bring misfortunes to the Republic's people. The 
recent intensification of the aggression is yet another 
confirmation of Armenia's [words indistinct]. 
  Armenia is making an effort to occupy new areas in 
Azerbaijan 
in total disregard of the peaceful initiatives made by several 
international organizations and foreign countries. Massing 
reinforcements and heavy military hardware, the Armenian Armed 
Forces intensely shelled Azerbaijan's Kazakhskiy, Tauzskiy, and 
Akstafa Rayons and the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic's Sadarak 
Rayon with rocket launchers and artillery units during the past 
few days. The wave of shelling began on 26 December. More 
than 100 Grad rockets and (?artillery shells) fell on 
Azerbaijan's peaceful border towns and several quarters in 
Kazakh City. Consequently, many peaceful people have been 
killed and several schools, medical centers, and means of 
transportation have been destroyed. 
  The Armenian Armed Forces, supported with armored vehicles, 
have prepared to launch an attack from the previously occupied 
Agderinskiy, Agdamskiy, and Fizulinskiy Rayons. Regardless of 
the losses they have suffered in their attacks earlier, they 
have not abandoned their attempts. In addition to the acts of 
violence, our republic is also being subjected to a ferocious 
propaganda campaign, which is being waged not only by Armenia's 
media organs but also by the parliament of that republic. The 
objective behind their unfounded statements and reports is to 
camouflage Armenia's policy of aggression against Azerbaijan and 
mislead the world on the situation. 
  The Azerbaijan Ministry of Foreign Affairs is convinced that 
Armenia will be completely responsible for the consequences of 
the intensified aggression against Azerbaijan. The aggression 
will lead to new losses and create additional misfortunes for 
the peoples of the two countries. 
  Azerbaijan urges the United Nations and international 
organizations to condemn Armenia's aggression and impose 
political and economic sanctions against that republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

