<H3> <TI>   Yerevan Accused of Escalating Hostilities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112170793 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1557 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3112170793 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani Foreign Ministry has accused 
Armenia of escalating hostilities in Nagorno-Karabakh. In its 
statement published today, the ministry points out that this "is 
another evidence of the annexationist policy" pursued by Yerevan. 
  The ministry stated that "all responsibility for the new 
round of hostilities entirely rests with Armenia whose actions 
doom the people of Azerbaijan and its own people to new victims 
and sufferings" calling on the world community to condemn the 
Armenian aggression and impose efficient political and economic 
sanctions against it. 
  The statement points out that the Armenian side neglects 
peacekeeping efforts by both international organizations and 
individual states attempting to seize more territories of 
Azerbaijan. 
  The ministry said Armenians had been shelling and rocketing 
the bordering districts of Azerbaijan situated in the north-west 
of the republic since December 26 as well as the village of 
Sadarak belonging to the Nakhichevan autonomous republic. 
Armenian units undertook an attempt to launch an offensive on 
the north and south of Azerbaijan. The ministry said civilian 
villages suffered heavy damages from hundreds of shells and 
rockets leaving victims and destroying homes, schools, hospitals 
and transport communications. 

</TEXT>

