<H3> <TI>   Turkey Against Shipping Oil Through Bosporus </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3112221293 Baku TURAN in English 1948 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC3112221293 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (December 31) TURAN -- "Ankara will not agree 
to ship the oil tankers through the Bosporus", said the 
Ambassador of Turkey to Azerbaijan, Altan Karamanoglu, to a 
Turan's reporter. 
  The matters concerning the ways of Azeri and, in prospect, 
Kazakhstani oil to Europe has yet to be considered. Russia 
suggests that oil should be shipped to the Black Sea's port of 
Novorossiysk and then by tankers to Europe. However, Turkey 
disagrees saying that this variant is oecologically dangerous. 
  "We can not put at stake ten-million Stambul city", said the 
Ambassador Karamanoglu. 
  Turkey as well as a number of the countries suggest that 
Azeri oil should be shipped to the port of Iskenderun 
(Mediterranean Sea) through the oil pipe-line and then by 
tankers to Europe. Azerbaijan insists on laying the pipe-line 
through Iran, Nakhichevan and Turkey. 

</TEXT>

