<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Cooperation Protocol Signed With Turkey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012153293 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1505 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012153293 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Feoktistov] </F>
  [Text] Ankara December 30 TASS -- A protocol on economic 
cooperation between Turkey and Russia was signed here on 
Thursday [30 December]. The document envisages cooperation in 
the power industry, transport, communications, construction, and 
new technologies. As regards the expansion of contacts, much 
importance is being attached to the private sector. 
  During the talks in Ankara, the two sides considered the 
state of affairs not only in traditional areas of cooperation 
but in new ones as well. These include satellite communication 
systems, advanced technologies, and defence industry conversion, 
Valeriy Mikhailov, Russian first deputy minister of economics, 
who leads a Russian delegation, told ITAR-TASS. 
  In future, it is essential to develop cooperation at the 
level of Turkish and Russian firms and in third countries, 
Mikhailov emphasised. 

</TEXT>

