<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Spokesman Compares Landsbergis With Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0201171294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1531 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0201171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia's Foreign Ministry is not inclined to "take 
seriously" numerous statements by the leader of Lithuania's 
parliamentary opposition, Vytautas Landsbergis. To argue with 
him is as pointless as with the leader of the Russian Liberal 
Democratic Party, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy. This is how a 
high-ranking Russian diplomat dealing with Baltic problems 
commented on Landsbergis's recent statements concerning 
relations with Russia. 
  Addressing a news conference in Vilnius recently, 
Landsbergis 
criticized the present Lithuanian leadership for its "policy of 
rapprochement with the East". According to him, the "aggressive 
nationalism of Russia, whose policy had been identical to that 
of Zhirinovskiy who only speaks more openly, revealed itself in 
full lately". 
  "Such escapades on the part of Landsbergis no longer 
surprise 
anyone," said Interfax's interviewee. "They have become so 
biased and subjective, that they can hardly be taken seriously 
even in Lithuania itself," he noted. 
  The interview with the Russian diplomat will be published in 
more detail in tomorrow's edition of Diplomatic Panorama. 

</TEXT>

