<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Signs Edict on Oil Field Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112153093 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0300 
GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112153093 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian head of state has issued an edict on 
securing order at oil-prospecting areas on the territory of the 
Republic of Georgia. 
  As from the beginning of 1994, oil prospecting, which will 
contribute to bringing the country out of the energy crisis, is 
planned to be carried out with the participation of foreign 
firms in the territory of the Republic of Georgia. In order to 
secure order at geological survey sites at the oil fields: 
  1. Full responsibility for the security of people engaged in 
work at the oil fields and the establishment of order in the 
corresponding areas will be given to the Georgian Ministry of 
Internal Affairs. The Ministry of Internal Affairs and the 
state Georgian Petroleum will sign an appropriate agreement and 
create proper conditions for police sub-units to carry out the 
assignment. 
  2. The Ministry of Internal Affairs will prevent any 
attempts 
by armed formations to obstruct establishment of proper order at 
oil- prospecting sites and refining installations. 
  3. The Georgian Ministry of Justice and the Procurator's 
Office will examine the state of the management of security at 
the installations and submit propositions about appropriate 
amendments to be introduced in the legislation to the Georgian 
parliament and the Georgian head of state. 
  [Signed] Eduard Shevardnadze 

</TEXT>

