<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Accused of Violating UN Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0101215994 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1700 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0101215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY, Tengiz 
Sharmanishvili, deputy chairman of the Committee for Interethnic 
Relations and Human Rights, sent a letter to the Georgian 
Foreign Ministry. 
  The letter says: Russian news sources have recently 
circulated news of the Russian Government's decision to lift the 
economic sanctions imposed on Abkhazia. As of now, Abkhazia's 
towns and villages are receiving electricity without hindrance. 
  The Abkhaz committee for human rights and interethnic 
relations states that the Abkhaz side has several times breached 
the clauses of the Geneva memorandum on mutual understanding 
signed by Georgia and Abkhazia; it has not stopped combat 
actions against Georgians in the Kodori gorge, is settling 
scores atrociously with the peaceful Georgian population in the 
Gali rayon, and is not taking any measures for finding those 
missing and reburying the killed; it is doing virtually nothing 
for the return of those evicted from their own land. 
  The Russian Government's new year gift is nothing less than 
a 
breach of Resolution No. 876 of the UN Security Council and 
casts doubt on the implementation of the Geneva memorandum on 
mutual understanding. 

</TEXT>

