<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interpol National Center Head Appointed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112103093 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0300 
GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112103093 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian Internal Affairs Ministry has become a 
member of Interpol. By Georgian Interior Minister Shota 
Kviraia's order, Police Major Giorgiy Aleksidze has been 
appointed the head of the Georgian Bureau of Interpol National 
Center. 
  Giorgiy Aleksidze was born in 1962. He graduated from 
Tbilisi State University. He has held the office of the head of 
a department in the Georgian Security Ministry. He has a 
perfect command of the French and English languages. 

</TEXT>

