<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bizhan Says Ukraine Signed No Military Accords in Ashgabat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0201211694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 
2 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0201211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Radio Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense </F>
Ministry] 
  [Text] Ukraine did not sign any military agreements at the 
meeting of CIS heads of state in Ashgabat in December last year. 
Colonel General Ivan Bizhan, Ukraine's deputy defense minister, 
said the Ukrainian military delegation's aim was to establish 
personal contacts with colleagues from CIS countries. Military 
accords will be signed in the near future with Kazakhstan and 
Uzbekistan. 

</TEXT>

