<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Broadcasts New Year's Messages </TI></H3>
<H4>   Greets Servicemen in Sarajevo </H4>
<F P=102> LD0101102894 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
0900 GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0101102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Leonid Kravchuk, the supreme commander of the Armed 
Forces and president of Ukraine, has sent New Year's greetings 
to the servicemen of the independent special battalion of 
Ukraine in the Sarajevo sector. 
  The state attributes great significance to your peace-making 
mission in the troubled region enveloped in the flames of war, 
says the message of greetings. The whole of Ukraine is 
following the events in former Yugoslavia with anxiety and 
unremitting attention. It is proud of the courage and restraint 
with which the soldiers of the Ukrainian battalion perform their 
humane duty. 
  Excellent actions by the Ukrainian battalion aimed at 
achieving peace on the long-suffering land, the message further 
reads, help establish our state on the world scene and promote 
the solution of many problems facing Ukraine in international 
relations. 
  The supreme commander of the Armed Forces of Ukraine wished 
the officers and soldiers of the battalion happiness, health, 
balance, and courage in their difficult and responsible service. 
  A New Year's message addressed to the same battalion has 
been 
sent by Army General Vitaliy Radetskyy, the Ukrainian defense 
minister. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

