<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Inflation Reached 70 Percent a Month in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0201204694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
2000 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0201204694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Cabinet of Ministers has instructed 
that all retail trade prices in the republic are to be rounded 
off to multiples of 10 as of 1 January. All trading 
organizations, whatever their form of ownership, are obliged, as 
previously, to accept one, three, and five coupon notes, 
although in future they will be withdrawn from circulation. 
  Official sources say inflation in Ukraine reached 70 percent 
a month by the end of 1993, and the largest bank note, 100,000 
karbovantsy, is worth approximately $3 at the market rate. 

</TEXT>

