<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Gives Greetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112190893 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1700 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112190893 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] You are watching Vesti. Russia's foreign minister 
[Andrey Kozyrev] is the next to give us his New Year's greetings. 
  [Begin Kozyrev recording] I would like to wish the residents 
of Russia more self-assurance. If we begin to respect 
ourselves, the whole world will respect us -- there are ample 
opportunities for that. Therefore, more self-esteem and less 
panic! Do not succumb to any provocations. Let us simply live 
normally in our own country, cooperate normally with other 
countries, and be the way we ought to be, the way we really are. 
  I think this, in fact, is my wish for 1994 -- that it should 
be a year of stabilization and a year which should see the 
transformation of Russia into a normal, self-respecting great 
power. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

