<H3> <TI>   Yablokov Explains Duties Following Dismissal by Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012135493 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1135 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012135493 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aleksey Yablokov has told INTERFAX that he is 
leaving the inner circle of the President, but gets a chance to 
normally deal with matters which prompted him to enter the 
system. 
  On Wednesday President Yeltsin dismissed Yablokov from the 
post of advisor on environmental and health matters and 
appointed him the chairman of a mixed environmental safety 
commission of the Russian Security Council. 
  "That was my request, Yablokov stressed. Lately I could not 
work effectively enough. I said that to the president, implying 
that he did not take much interest in environmental matters 
either." Yablokov said that the decisions of the mixed 
commission will be compulsory for discussion, unlike the 
recommendations of a presidential advisor. 

</TEXT>

