<H3> <TI>   Filatov Sets Up Analytical `Council of Experts' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0201165094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1251 
GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0201165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 2 Jan -- Sergey Filatov, President Yeltsin's 
head of staff, is currently working on the creation of an 
analytical council of experts to provide practical assistance to 
the president in the performance of his constitutional duties, 
he said in an interview with ITAR-TASS. 
  According to the chief of staff, the three analytical 
centers 
that used to work separately to the president will shortly be 
reorganized into a single unit. This unit, or council of 
experts, will concentrate all analysis coming in from the 
various research structures and draw up recommendations for the 
president, the government, and Russian regional leaders. 
  The council of experts, as the prototype for a future 
administration of the head of state, will work on the 
president's special programs and on his yearly greetings 
messages. 

</TEXT>

