<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Election Aftermath </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Constitution Prerequisite for Stability </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301114894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1125 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0301114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 3 TASS -- The press secretary of the 
Russian president, Vyacheslav Kostikov, answered questions in an 
interview with ITAR-TASS on Monday. 
  Question: What are the main principles and tasks of the 
Russian president in 1994? 
  Answer: The domineering prerequisite of stability in 1994 is 
the new Russian Constitution. I would like to point out that 
the Constitution is reliably protected by the free will of the 
people and that the president, as a guarantor of the 
Constitution, has a reliable mechanism for its protection. The 
main political task of President Boris Yeltsin is the 
realisation of the new Constitution both in the Russian state 
system and relying on basic democratic provisions of the 
Constitution. 
  Question: What will the president's relations with the 
Federal Assembly rely on? 
  Answer: In its relations with the Federal Assembly the 
president will act in alliance with all political forces 
interested in the protection of Russia's interests and the 
development of its reforms. The character of this interaction 
will depend on an extent to which political parties and blocs 
represented in the Federal Assembly show respect for Russia's 
constitutional will and on what lessons participants in a 
political dialogue learned from past experience. 
  Rejecting the practice of confrontation, the president is 
prepared to take advantage of all powers granted to him by the 
Constitution to defend democracy, reforms, Russia's integrity 
and stability. 
  Question: What do you believe to be main priorities of 
Russia's state policy in 1994? 
  Answer: In the economic policy, priority will be given to 
strengthening factors of financial stability, curbing inflation 
rates, strengthening the rouble and giving support to a sound 
industrial base. 
  In the social policy, the emphasis will be laid on the 
protection of the population from criminals and the creation of 
fair and worthy conditions for honest and peaceful labour. 
  Undoubtedly, the Russian foreign policy will lay the 
emphasis 
on the protection of Russia's national interests, the rights of 
the Russian and the Russian-speaking population in the framework 
of international law and proceeding from the idea of national 
solidarity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

