<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Election Aftermath </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders Continue Discussions of Duma Chairperson </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112171293 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1629 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3112171293 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Leaders of Russia's electoral blocs and political 
parties on Friday held a new meeting in the Kremlin to discuss 
candidacies to the posts of chairperson and deputy chairpersons 
of the State Duma, the lower house of the new parliament. 
  Well-informed sources told Interfax the meeting was attended 
by Yegor Gaydar (Russia's Choice), Grigory Yavlinsky (the 
Yavlinsky-Boldyrev-Lukin bloc), Vladimir Zhirinovsky (the 
Liberal Democratic Party), Nikolay Travkin (the Democratic 
Party), Yekaterina Lakhova (the Union of Women of Russia), 
Mikhail Lapshin (the Agrarian Party), and Gennadiy Zyuganov (the 
Communist Party). Nobody from the Party of Russian Unity and 
Concord was present, however. 
  The next meeting has been scheduled for January 4. 

</TEXT>

