<H3> <TI>   PRAVDA Prepared To Join Newspaper Strike </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM3112105993 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 31 Dec 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM3112105993 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vadim Gorshenin: "PRAVDA Prepared To Join </F>
Strike"] 
  [Text] After the destruction of the Supreme Soviet and the 
abolition of the Security Ministry it is the press' turn to face 
heavy shelling. If the Chernomyrdin government decree is 
fulfilled prices for newspapers will increase substantially. 
Yesterday your PRAVDA correspondent got in touch with Ivan 
Laptev, president of the association of chief editors and 
publishers. 
  "I should like to draw the attention of PRAVDA employees and 
readers," Ivan Dmitriyevich stated. "It is not a case of 
dependent or independent publications -- it was a case of the 
economic stifling of the entire press. And unless the president 
and government repeal decree no. 1233, then soon we shall have 
only memories of the press. Incidentally, I should like to note 
that the decision which has been taken discredits the new 
Constitution, especially article 29." 
  For our readers' information. PRAVDA, like many other 
Russian newspapers, states its readiness also to suspend the 
production of its publication from 10 through 17 January in 
protest against one more government pogrom. 

</TEXT>

