<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Creates Central Command for Border Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012144193 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1334 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3012144193 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Roman Zadunayskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 30 December -- Today, Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin signed an edict "On the formation of the Federal 
Border Service-Central Command of the Russian border troops." 
The ITAR-TASS correspondent learned this from Colonel Yevgeniy 
Znamenskiy, deputy head of the press office of the Russian 
border troops. The edict has been issued in connection with the 
dismantling of the Russian Ministry of Security and in order to 
ensure continuity of command of the Russian border troops. 
  The representative of the press office has also reported 
that 
under the decree, the Federal Border Service-Central Command of 
the Russian border troops is to a have a status equivalent to 
that of a Federal ministry and to operate in direct 
subordination to the Russian president and government. Colonel 
General Andrey Nikolayev has been appointed the commander in 
chief of Russia's border troops. 

</TEXT>

