<H3> <TI>   Said Dissatisfied With Generals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0101103094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0101103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dozens of generals' posts are to be cut in the 
Russian Ministry of Defense Main Personnel Directorate. 
According to ITAR-TASS, on the eve of the new year, Defense 
Minister Pavel Grachev expressed dissatisfaction with the 
directorate's activity at a meeting with journalists. In his 
opinion, under new conditions many personnel officers in 
generals' positions are still doing everything in an 
old-fashioned way, trying to work less with the soldiers and 
looking after higher command personnel better. At the same time 
the head of the military department was not uncomplimentary 
about the lower echelons of the army personnel department, which 
work with sergeants and other ranks. The reform will not affect 
the interests of this category of officer. 

</TEXT>

