<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army's New Military Emblem Unveiled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012204693 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012204693 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Moscow Ostankino Television First 
Channel Network in Russian at 1800 GMT on 30 December broadcasts 
an item in the "Novosti" newscast in which Aleksandr Ukhov 
reports from Moscow that the Russian Army will be getting a new 
emblem next year. The Moscow Ostankino channel presents what it 
calls "the first pictures" of the new emblem. 
  Ukhov says that the Russian Defense Ministry recently 
organized a competition for a new emblem for the Russian Army. 
Almost 300 proposals were submitted for consideration. The 
results of the competition have recently been announced. The 
new emblem will consist of a crowned double-headed eagle holding 
a laurel wreath and sword. On an inset shield mounted on the 
eagle's chest a horseman can be seen killing a dragon. The 
eagle clutches the Russian national flag and the St. Andrew's 
flag in its claws. 
  A brief interview with V.N.Medvedev, head of the insignia 
department of the Ministry of Defense General Staff 
Headquarters, is then shown. He says: "There are plans for 
placing this unified emblem of the Russian Armed Forces on 
military uniforms, banners of military units, military and navy 
flags, identification marks on military equipment, documents and 
identity cards." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

