<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Says Import Tariffs Deferred Until March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM3012140393 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 30 Dec 93 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> PM3012140393 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["At the Center of Attention" news column report] </F>
  [Text] There will be no introduction of import tariffs on 
goods from 1 January 1994, Yegor Gaydar, first vice premier of 
the Russian Federation stated. The corresponding government 
decree has been deferred for further processing, and it is 
planned to introduce import tariffs from 1 March. At the same 
time Ye. Gaydar stressed that the bulk of goods and agricultural 
produce comes onto the Russian market from the CIS countries, 
with the majority of which free trade agreements exist. No 
duties will be introduced on these goods and products. 

</TEXT>

