<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry on Reductions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0401101794 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0800 
GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0401101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Belarusian Defense Ministry told a BELINFORM 
correspondent that a distinctive feature of the Belarusian Armed 
Forces this year would be completing the second stage of their 
reorganization. The former Belarusian Military District will 
continue to reduce its forces, which until recently numbered 
about 250,000 servicemen, and was an unbearable burden to the 
state budget. In addition, according to the new Belarusian 
military doctrine based on the nonnuclear status, the size of 
the Armed Forces should be reduced to the levels sufficient only 
to defend the country's sovereignty and security. The size of 
the Belarusian Army is expected to shrink to 100,000 servicemen 
within the year. 

</TEXT>

