<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Introduces Emergency Measures To Curb Inflation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401110994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As ITAR-TASS reports, emergency measures have been 
taken in Kazakhstan to lower inflation. Wages and all types of 
bonus payments in the republic are now being strictly linked to 
the amount and quality of labor. By doing this, the leadership 
of Kazakhstan hopes to stop the practice of adjusting money 
payments to cover inflation. The new procedure for payments is 
compulsory for all enterprises. Inspection bodies have been 
given the right to withdraw from consumption funds any unmerited 
sums that have been paid out and to transfer them to local 
budget revenues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

