<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Zone To Be Set Up on Chinese Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401102094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0250 
GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Oreshin] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 4 Jan (ITAR-TASS) -- Representatives of 
Amur Oblast and the Chinese border town of Heihe have signed an 
agreement on setting up a zone of international trade and 
economic cooperation. 
  The 20 square km zone will be situated on both banks of the 
Amur River. Within the zone it is intended to open up trade and 
banking institutions and industrial enterprises using advanced 
technology and to set up a developed infrastructure. In 
particular, it is planned to build a road bridge. 
  The economic zone will become a base for processing products 
targeted at the markets not only of Russia and China but also of 
other countries. It will have free circulation of goods and 
free currency exchange and it will be managed by a joint 
committee with the participation of representatives of the 
Russian Federation and the PRC. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

