<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Social Democrats Request Help for Russian-Speaking Citizens </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301160294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1500 GMT 
3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0301160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The mass media in Kyrgyzstan have today published an 
open letter from the political council of the republic's Social 
Democratic Party [SDP] to the presidents of Russia and 
Kyrgyzstan. The main reason for this, in the view of the Social 
Democrats, is the considerable deterioration in the people's 
standard of living, the Russian-speaking citizens' increasing 
loss of confidence that they will be given social protection, 
and their worry for their children's future. 
  Given this, the SDP has called upon the presidents of Russia 
and Kyrgyzstan to ensure that industrial enterprises of the two 
countries that have mutual economic ties are granted most 
favored status, in order to avoid bankruptcy and mass unrest 
among the people; to draw up and adopt a law on immigration 
based upon international norms and rights; and to guarantee that 
Russian-speaking citizens in Kyrgyzstan may receive education in 
the Russian language; and finally to conclude an 
inter-governmental agreement on recognizing dual citizenship in 
Russia and Kyrgyzstan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

