<H3> <TI>   Academy of Sciences Head Urges Support for Akayev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401105194 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 0000 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kyrgyz </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The referendum day scheduled for 30 January by 
President Askar Akayev is approaching. In this connection, our 
correspondent interviewed Turar Koychiyev, president of the 
Kyrgyz Academy of Sciences. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified correspondent] Turar 
Koychiyev, what do you think about President Akayev's decision 
to hold the referendum? 
  [Koychiyev] I think it is a necessary step. We are building 
democracy in our society, and I think that Akayevich is 
absolutely correct because it is a very important political 
question. The president needs to know the public's opinion. 
Our reform process seems to be developing. The path chosen for 
our development is diametrically opposed to what we had before. 
I think we passed one important stage in these three years and 
are finding ourselves at the second stage of our social and 
economic development. Our president is doing his best to 
improve the situation in the country. On 30 January, those who 
want (?equality) and prosperity for Kyrgyzstan should support 
President Akayev's policy. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

