<H3> <TI>   Supreme Soviet Officials Meet With Dostam Representatives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301132194 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 0500 
GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0301132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tajik </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tohir Ahmadov and Sangmuhammad Zuhurov, leaders of 
the working group of the Republic of Tajikistan Supreme Soviet's 
commission on refugees, met with Major General Sufi Manan and 
Major General Nur Mohammad, representatives of Abdol Rashid 
Dostam, leader of the National and Islamic Movement of 
Afghanistan, in Sher Khan Bandar at the request of the Afghan 
side. 
  During the meeting, the Afghan side informed the Tajik side 
that in accordance with an agreement signed between the official 
Kabul government and the Islamic National Movement of 
Afghanistan it has been decided that Sher Khan Bandar will be 
transferred to the representatives of Abdol Rashid Dostam. 
  Questions concerning the repatriation of Tajik refugees were 
also discussed. The Afghan representatives said that in 1994 
they will take all the necessary measures to speed up the 
repatriation of refugees and to guarantee their security. In 
addition, a transit camp will soon be opened near the Sher Khan 
Bandar. 

</TEXT>

