<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian President Levon Ter-Petrosyan signed a 
decree today on (?raising) the minimum wages, wages of employees 
working in state enterprises, tuitions, benefits, and pensions 
in Armenia. 
  The decree says in particular: Taking into account the need 
for the additional measures to provide social protection to the 
people in view of sharp increase in prices, I hereby decide: 
  To establish the minimum wage in Armenia at 110 dram as of 1 
January 1994, the wages of (?civil servants) [words indistinct] 
at 121 dram, and the [passage indistinct]. 
  To increase threefold the pensions within the 36.7 and 73.8 
dram bracket in Armenia [words indistinct], and increase the 
pensions above 73.8 dram by 146 dram. 
  To establish the allowances for young persons within 7-17 
age 
group at (35) dram per month. 
  The full text of the decree will be published in HAYASTANI 
HANRAPETUTYUN. 

