<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Food, Service Prices Fixed on 4 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0301213694 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 2000 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0301213694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 2000 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In order to expand commodity circulation in the 
consumer market and reduce production (?losses), the Armenian 
Government has decided to establish new retail prices for bread, 
flour, and basic services as of 4 January. The retail price of 
bread has been fixed at 1.50 dram, or 300 rubles, per kilo; 
flour at 1.21 dram, or 250 rubles, per kilo. The rate for 
electricity has been fixed at .20 dram, or 40 rubles per 
kilowatt-hour. Inter-city passenger transportation on buses, 
trolleys, and trams has been fixed at .50 dram, or 100 rubles, 
per person. 
  The cost of basic services--such as rent, water, garbage 
collection, and telephone service--have also been increased by 
an average of two-and-a-half times more than their previous cost. 
  Detailed information will be published in the press. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

