<H3> <TI>   Communists Call For Unity With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3012152593 Yerevan SNARK in English 0903 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC3012152593 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, December 29 (SNARK) -- The Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of Armenia has called on people 
to unite the efforts of the normal layers of society to restore 
the new political, military and economic unit with Russia. In 
its New Year's statement communists called upon to the creation 
of the coalition government of the national agreement, demanded 
to stop the privatization's process and purchase and sale of 
land. 
  By spring, as Armenian communists consider, it is necessary 
to undertake pre-scheduled presidency and parliament's elections. 
  Vladimir Darbinyan, the member of the board of Central 
Committee of Communist Party of Armenia, said to SNARK that 
these requirements is for national interests of Armenian people, 
the future of which impossible to imagine out of the new union 
of republics, recreated voluntary. 
  Meanwhile, during his recent interview to SNARK Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan excluded the possibility to recreate the Union. 

</TEXT>

