<H3> <TI>   Armenian Army Supplied With Artillery in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0301161594 Baku TURAN in English 1419 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0301161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (January 3) TURAN--As TURAN agency was told by 
the military sources, fightings in the north of Karabakh 
continue. Armenian Army is supplied with military hardware and 
artillery. 
  Last night Armenian Army tried to take back top-hills and 
settlements of the region, which they have lost the day before. 
  At the same time, Armenian units tried to search the region 
round Omar crossing (the border between Kelbadzharskiy and 
Khanlarskiy regions of Azerbaijan), however, they have retreated 
having ten dead and wounded soldiers. 

</TEXT>

