<H3> <TI>   Further on Message </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0301162894 Baku TURAN in English 1419 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0301162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (January 3) TURAN--On December 31 in his 
televised address to the nation, Azerbaijani President Aliyev 
said that in 1994 all the territories occupied by Armenian Army 
would be liberated. He stressed that this goal should be 
achieved in spite of all losses. 
  The President Aliyev said that there have been positive 
changes in Azeri Army recently. For the last month in the 
course of firings Armenian Army could not break the Azeri 
defense. According to the president, these are the consequences 
of the measures taken by the government in the field of military 
building. 
  Azerbaijan comes out for peaceful means of settlement of the 
Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict and it will continue to adhere to 
this policy in the nearest future, the President Aliyev said. 

</TEXT>

