<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev, Russian Commander Discuss Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0301163594 Baku TURAN in English 1448 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0301163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 30, TURAN--Colonel-General Andrey 
Nikolayev-the commander of the Russian frontier troops is 
visiting Baku. Today at 4 p.m. General Nikolayev was received 
by President Aliyev. As a reliable source at the presidential 
staff told TURAN agency the questions of the further on 
cooperation between Russia and Azerbaijan in the guarding of the 
southern borders of the CIS were discussed at the meeting. 
  Last November Nikolayev told journalists in Moscow that 
Azerbaijan had appealed to Moscow with a proposal of the 
cooperative guarding of the southern borders and this question 
is being working out at present. But the official Baku rejected 
this report then. 
  During the today's meeting Andrey Nikolayev said, that the 
parties intend to discuss the problems of the cooperative 
guarding of the southern borders of the CIS. 
  In his turn, Geydar Aliyev said that Azerbaijan would like 
to 
solve the problems of guarding its borders in complex. For 
Azerbaijan the guarding of the border with Armenian is much more 
important than the guarding of border with the other states, he 
said. In this connection he pointed out, that 170 km of 
Azerbaijani-Iranian border is under the control of the Armenian 
Army. 
  After this the meeting went on behind closed doors. 

</TEXT>

