<H3> <TI>   Yavlinskiy Denies Rumors of Government Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301150294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1430 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0301150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 3 TASS -- Well-known Russian 
economist Grigory Yavlinskiy, one of the leaders of a democratic 
electoral coalition, told ITAR-TASS on Monday that rumors 
circulating in the mass media that he was offered a job as 
chairman of the Anti-Monopoly Committee were completely false. 
  Such rumors apparently arose from the fact that Yavlinskiy 
was asked to propose an appropriate candidate for that post. "We 
were talking about strengthening the Anti-Monopoly Committee, 
but there was no question of my appointment," he asserted. 

</TEXT>

