<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Media Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Editors Threaten Strike To Protest Costs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401121894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1125 
GMT 4 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 4 Jan--Journalists of major newspapers are 
prepared to suspend their publications beginning 11 January. 
This protest action against the government's decision to 
reevaluate the assets of national economic enterprises was 
announced at a news conference today. 
  Editors in chief of KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA, MOSKOVSKAYA 
PRAVDA, 
VECHERNYAYA MOSKVA, MOSKOVSKIYE NOVOSTI, NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA, 
and many other publications said that Resolution No. 1233 of 25 
December would result in a 600 percent increase in printing 
costs and would, in fact, be tantamount to stifling the press. 
  Journalists' unions of Russia and Moscow, the Association of 
Publishers and Editors in Chief, and the Fund for the Defense of 
Glasnost have demanded the following: that purpose-built 
allowances to publications be earmarked in order to continue 
issuing the numbers of copies prepaid by subscribers; that a 
special procedure for the implementation of the resolution in 
printing and communications industries be introduced; and that 
editorial collectives be offered real possibilities for 
privatizing printing works and related facilities. 
  Stressing that the planned action was a forced measure, 
Vsevolod Bogdanov, chairman of the Union of Journalists of 
Russia, voiced the hope that the government would go halfway 
toward meeting the journalists' demands in the very near future. 
He said that a final decision on carrying out the action will 
be made tomorrow. Furthermore, the majority of regional 
publications in Russia are ready to participate. Radio and 
television journalists will back their colleagues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

