<H3> <TI>   Russian Military Facilities Returned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0301162294 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1500 GMT 3 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0301162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ilgonis Upmalis, head of the Latvian bureau for 
monitoring the Russian troop withdrawal, reported today that the 
Russian 15th Air-force Army handed over to Latvia the army 
headquarters on Brivibas Street and the training center on 
Slokas Street in Riga at the end of December. 
  According to a decision by a government commission, the 
Rosme 
state-owned joint stock company took over the headquarters 
building as its property and the Civil Defense and the Technical 
University of Riga took over the training center. 
  According to Upmalis, the 15th Air-force Army has been 
disbanded and the majority of its military facilities have 
already been handed over to Latvia. The airfields at Lielvarde 
and Daugavpils, an army command post at Adazi, as well as 
several facilities in Riga have not yet been handed over. 

</TEXT>

