<H3> <TI>   Tatarstan President Issues New Year's Greetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3112215893 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1605 
GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3112215893 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Sorokin] </F>
  [Text] Kazan, 31 Dec -- Tatarstan President Mintimer 
Shaymiyev today addressed New Year's greetings to his fellow 
countrymen. After expressing his best wishes, he said the people 
are coping well with the trials of the early years of transition 
to market conditions. Although farmers have gathered in a fine 
harvest, a difficult situation has taken shape in that sphere, 
as well as in some others, owing to failure to pay. The 
president is confident that all these hardships are temporary 
and will be overcome through joint efforts. A policy which 
regards social programs as a priority is being pursued in the 
republic. 
  Talking about the relations with Russia, Tatarstan's 
president said: "We are continuing consistent work aimed at 
reaching various agreements, taking into account the 
achievements made by Tatarstan on the civilized route toward 
establishing its statehood." Such is the will of the people, 
President Shaymiyev concluded. 
  Wishing his countrymen a happy new year, he told them to 
strengthen links of blood and spirit between one another. 

</TEXT>

