<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electoral Commission Schedules New Elections </TI></H3>
<H4>   Decree on Chelyabinsk </H4>
<F P=102> PM3112133193 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 31 Dec 93 
First Edition p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PM3112133193 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation Central Electoral Commission decree No. </F>
159 "On the Additional Nomination of Candidate deputies of the 
Russian Federation Federal Assembly Federation Council in 
Chelyabinsk No. 74 Two-Seat Electoral District"] 
  [Text] At the end of the registration of candidate 
deputies of the Russian Federation Federal Assembly Federation 
Council in Chelyabinsk No. 74 two-seat electoral district for 
the elections to the Federation Council fewer than three 
candidates were registered. 
  In connection with the need for the additional nomination of 
candidate deputies for this district, the Russian Federation 
Central Electoral Commission on the basis of point 7 article 20 
of the Statute on the Elections of Russian Federation Federal 
Assembly Federation Council deputies in 1993 decrees: 
  1. That the election of Federation Council deputies in 
Chelyabinsk No. 74 two-seat electoral district be scheduled for 
26 March 1994 for the additional nomination of candidates and 
the implementation of subsequent electoral actions. 
  2. That the organization and holding of the elections be 
assigned to the Chelyabinsk No. 74 two-seat electoral district 
commission for the election of the Russian Federation Federal 
Assembly Federation Council deputies and to the relevant polling 
place electoral commissions as previously staffed, at the same 
polling places and on the basis of the same voters lists with 
the necessary amendments and additions which have been 
introduced to them. 
  The announcement of the additional nomination of candidates 
and the date of the elections should be published in the press. 
  [Signed] N.T. Ryabov, chairman of the Russian federation 
Central Electoral commission; V.A. Zagulyayev, secretary of the 
Russian Federation Central Electoral Commission 
  [Dated] Moscow, 25 December 1993 

</TEXT>

