<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dzasokhov Withdraws From North Ossetia Election Campaign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0201185494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1842 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0201185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz January 2 TASS -- "I withdraw my 
candidature in the presidential election campaign for the sake 
of further consolidation of society and victory of the North 
Ossetian sound forces," ex-secretary of the Soviet Communist 
Party Central Committee and State Duma deputy from Northern 
Ossetia Aleksandr Dzasokhov told the North Ossetian TV news 
program today. 
  "I am grateful to all North Ossetian electors who supported 
my candidature at the Russian presidential elections. The new 
Russian parliament will have to work hard in the name of 
economic revival of the country and its indivisibility. My 
hopes are pinned on the new Russian constitution approved by the 
people," he said. 
  Speaking of the North Ossetian presidential elections 
scheduled for January 16, Dzasokhov noted the supreme official 
should personify the spirit of accord and well-wishing in the 
multi- national republic. Any social-economic policy can be 
successful only on this basis. 
  "I would wish the future North Ossetian president to be more 
active in solution of personnel issues and combine experience 
and youth. When introducing the presidency in Northern Ossetia, 
we should clearly decide on our foreign and domestic policy, 
development of the social sphere and perfection of inter-ethnic 
relations," added Dzasokhov. 

</TEXT>

