<H3> <TI>   North Ossetia, Center Disagree Over Fulfilling Decisions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0401095594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 4 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0401095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [RIA report: "Moscow Is Far Away but Voters Are Nearby"] </F>
  [Text] Viktor Chernomyrdin, chairman of the Russian 
Government, has sent the North Ossetia Government a number of 
instructions for fulfilling the decisions made 7 December 1993 
in Nalchik at the Russian president's conference with leaders of 
the North Caucasus republics, krays, and oblasts. 
  But at a North Ossetia Security council sesion Akhsarbek 
Galazov, chairman of the republic's Supreme Soviet, stated that 
"a number of instructions which North Ossetia is now being 
obliged to fulfill were not examined at all at the Nalchik 
conference." In the opinion of local observers this divergent 
interpretation of the documents adopted in the capital of 
Kabardino-Balkaria is connected with the forthcoming 16 January 
elections of the North Ossetia president. If the public finds 
out that a representative of North Ossetia has nonetheless 
approved the final document in Nalchik, he will lose support 
among voters.. 

</TEXT>

