<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attacks Continue in North Ossetia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012131793 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1257 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012131793 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valery Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz December 30 TASS -- The situation in the 
state of emergency zone of Northern Ossetia remained complicated 
in the last days of the outgoing year. 
  According to military sources, a group of unidentified men 
repeatedly opened fire from automatic weapons and 
grenade-throwers on a customs post near the mountain village of 
Nizhny Lars, located on the Georgian military highway. Two 
agents of the North Ossetian Interior Ministry were wounded by 
grenade splinters. 
  Seven night-time gun battles were fought in several 
settlements of Prigorodny district. No casualities were 
reported. 
  According to information released by the investigation team 
of the Russian Interior Ministry, several submachine-guns, 
fourteen pistols, many grenades and explosive devices, some 
blank weapons, and hundreds of cartridges were discovered in a 
dwelling house in Malgobek district of the Ingush republic in 
the course of searches carried out there. 

</TEXT>

