<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry To Replace Peacekeeping Units in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0401101594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0900 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0401101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press service of the Defense Ministry has 
reported on the mechanism for the subsequent replacement of the 
Ukrainian peacekeeping battalion in former Yugoslavia. The 
personnel of the 420-strong unit is to be replaced during this 
and the following months. The battalion will be reinforced by 
another unit that will be entrusted by the command of blue 
helmets deployed in Bosnia, with controlling the vicinity of the 
city of Srebrenitsa. All of the Ukrainian draftees are 
volunteers and serve in the Odessa Military District. 
Currently, they are completing a special language course. 

</TEXT>

