<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Notes 1993 Events, `Numerous Problems' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0301165794 Tallinn BNS in English 1025 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0301165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 03, BNS - Lithuanian President 
Algirdas Brazauskas addressed his nation one hour before the 
year's end to wish every household good health, teamwork and 
creativity, joy and happiness. 
  He said that the year 1993 had seen numerous significant 
events such as withdrawal of Russian troops, introduction of a 
permanent national currency, state of the law and order reform 
and improved international prestige of the Lithuanian state. 
  The head of state said, however, that numerous problems 
would 
have to be faced in the economy, agriculture, manufacturing 
industries and other areas. 
  The Lithuanian president expressed the hope that they would 
be surmounted if the Seimas [parliament], the government and 
other power and management agencies worked responsibly for 
freedoms and rights, well-being and a better future of 
Lithuania's residents, if the new year saw less suspicion and 
hatred. 

</TEXT>

