<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Decree Orders Privatization of Gas Stations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012122093 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
2000 GMT 29 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3012122093 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Decree issued by President Leonid Kravchuk; date not given] </F>
  [Text] With the aim of stimulating activity to provide the 
general population with fuel and lubricants and establish the 
rules of privatizing gas stations that sell fuel and lubricants 
specifically to the general population and the plots of land 
these stations are situated on, and in compliance with item 
seven of Article 114/5 of the Constitution of Ukraine, I decree: 
  To carry out privatization of gas stations that sell fuel 
and 
lubricants specifically to the general population. Along with 
the privatization of the gas stations, the land on which they 
are situated will also be privatized. The right to the 
privatization of the gas stations and plots of land is vested in 
the citizens of Ukraine, foreign citizens, persons without 
citizenship, legal entities registered on the territory of 
Ukraine whose authorized fund contains no share of state 
property, and legal entities of foreign countries. 
  A decision on the privatization of gas stations is taken by 
the State Property Fund of Ukraine, its regional branches whose 
representations, with the participation of the State Committee 
of Ukraine for Land Resources and its bodies in the regions. 
These decisions are, at the same time, decisions on the 
privatization of plots of land. 
  The privatization of gas stations and plots of land will be 
carried out by auction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

