<H3> <TI>   Electoral Commission Registers Liberal Democratic Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401113694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0904 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev--The Central Electoral Commission registered 
the Liberal Democratic Party of Ukraine [LDPU] on 3 January as 
the 20th party that will nominate candidates during the upcoming 
elections to the Ukrainian parliament. As Volodymyr Klymchuk, 
the party's leader told a UNIAN correspondent, the "LDPU is 
cautious about forming blocs with other political forces. It 
is, above all, afraid of the efforts that have been announced by 
some blocs to form excessively rigid structures that could 
hinder the opportunity to operate independently. However, this 
does not mean that the liberal democrats will halt contacts and 
consultations with other parties." 
  According to Klymchuk, the communists and socialists are the 
only ones considered by the LDPU to be opponents. 

</TEXT>

