GMT 4 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 4 Jan--Only an interim version of standing 
orders will be ready for the first session of the Lower Chamber 
of the Federal Assembly, Grigoriy Bondarev, coordinator of the 
commission for standing orders and for the status of deputies of 
the State Duma, told ITAR-TASS today. 
  Bondarev said that "a certain temporary document" would be 
worked out by 11 January that will allow the State Duma to 
commence work. Later, according to Bondarev, the State Duma will 
form its own commission for standing orders, which will "prepare 
a document for all occasions". 

