<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Funding Allegations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0401105794 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 4 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0401105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report under the "Details" rubric: "Has the </F>
LDPR's Money Been Found?"] 
  [Text] ALGEMEEN DAGBLAD writes that the Dutch economic 
monitoring service and the Central Bank of Russia have decided 
to begin an investigation into an article in SEGODNYA according 
to which the GMM trust company, registered in the Netherlands, 
lent financial support to V. Zhirinovskiy during his election 
campaign in Russia. The political aspects are not the issue 
here, according to the newspaper, but possible violations of the 
law on granting credits. 
  Japan's SANKEI SHIMBUN, touching on press reports that the 
Dutch company GMM granted Zhirinovskiy's party $800,000 to fund 
its election expenses, remarks in its commentary: "So far there 
is no precise information suggesting the Dutch company's role in 
financing the LDPR [Liberal Democratic Party of Russia], but as 
of today it has been definitely confirmed that branches of the 
Zhirinovskiy party election campaign had premises in GMM 
advertising branches in Russia, and that the Dutch company's 
advertising and Zhirinovskiy's election campaign were funded 
from the same source. 
  "Light may be thrown on the Dutch firm's role in funding the 
LDPR in the near future, since the Netherlands Ministry of 
Finance has begun an investigation into GMM's activity, using as 
a pretext this firm's breach of national laws on security 
transactions." 

</TEXT>

