<H3> <TI>   Premier on Achieving Lower Prices for Oil, Gas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401182594 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Accords reached with Russia and Turkmenistan 
regarding oil and gas deliveries to Ukraine at prices 
considerably lower than they were in December 1993 make it 
certain that we will be able to make sure of stable work within 
industry. Yukhym Zvyahilskyy, acting prime minister of Ukraine, 
stated this in an interview with the press. He noted that the 
government is taking under its control the prices of oil 
products, and at what price they will be sold both to state and 
private firms. 

</TEXT>

