<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Meeting Discusses Stabilizing Industrial Branches </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401213394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2042 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401213394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Valentin Vernodubenko for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev January 4 TASS -- A Ukrainian Government 
meeting chaired by Acting Prime Minister Yefim Zvyagilskiy 
discussed today the stabilization of basic industrial branches. 
The meeting was attended by government members and heads of 
ministries and departments of the mining and coke-chemical 
industries, metallurgy, power engineering and transport. 
  "The discussion was suggested by a recent meeting of the 
Cabinet of Ministers that dwelt on prices on energy carriers, 
primarily coal," Ukrainian Vice-Premier Vasiliy Yevtukhov told 
UKRINFORM. 
  "We have raised coal prices, which resulted in the increase 
of prices on sausage, milk and bread. It is clear as soon as 
coal prices are raised, coke prices immediately go up, which is 
followed by price increase on machine-building and agricultural 
products. 
  "Some meeting speakers noted we can raise fuel prices and 
keep those in metallurgy and power engineering on the same 
level. It is impossible since the production costs in these 
branches include coal spending. The meeting aimed to reach a 
parity of prices in the coal industry, metallurgy and power 
engineering and achieve mutual understanding without which it is 
impossible to overcome the economic crisis," he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-54900 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov003_f_94004" </HT>


