<H3> <TI>   State Property Management Powers Delegated to Oblasts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WA0401224694 </F>
<F P=103> WA0401224694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Donetsk Television Network in Russian at 
1630 GMT on 9 December carries its regular "Novosti Donetchiny" 
program which contains an announcement about delegation of 
powers for management of state property to four oblast 
administrations starting 1 January 1994. 
  The anchorwoman says that Presidential Representative Yu. 
Smirnov has signed an instruction to organize the implementation 
of President Kravchuk's decree of 26 November on delegation of 
powers to Dnepropetrovsk, Donetsk, Zaporozhye and Lugansk Oblast 
Administrations for management of state property. As was 
explained to executive committees, city Soviets of People's 
Deputies, district state administrations and oblast directorates 
and departments, this measure is aimed at the stabilization of 
the economy, introduction of market relations, further 
development of these regions and enhancement of efficiency of 
management of state property. During the period from January 1, 
1994 to December 31, 1995, as an experiment, Donetsk State 
Administration will perform the functions of management of 
property of state enterprises, institutions and organizations. 

</TEXT>

