<H3> <TI>   Former Lvov Missile Base Sold to Private Firm </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401194694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1459 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lvov -- At a conference of the "Lvivprylad" 
production association on 3 January, Vasyl Dzera, chairman of 
the Frankivskyy rayon executive committee and a member of the 
oblast council commission for checking on foreign trade activity 
of the oblast state administration, asserted that the oblast 
authorities has sold a missile base near Brody to the private 
firm "Konza" for $13,000. 
  Apart from a missile silo the former nuclear base includes 
working independent thermal and power resources, purification 
structures, and independent power supply systems. According to 
Vasyl Dzera, the procurator general's office of Ukraine has 
instituted criminal proceedings regarding the sale of a former 
military facility by the oblast state administration to "Konza." 

</TEXT>

