<H3> <TI>   Kebich Departs for Moscow Talks With Cheromyrdin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401164394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1442 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav 
Kebich departed from Minsk for Moscow to meet with his Russian 
counterpart Viktor Chernomyrdin. The press service of the 
Belarusian premier reported to INTERFAX that the heads of the 
two governments intend to finally coordinate issues regarding 
unification of Russia's and Belarus' monetary systems. 
  To this effect, our INTERFAX correspondent in Belarus 
reported that a joint statement of the two governments was 
expected to be voiced in late December, 1993. 

</TEXT>

