<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belarus Lifts Foreign Travel Restrictions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2812165293 Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information in Russian 0734 GMT 28 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2812165293 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Law "On the Procedure of the Exit from and Entry 
into the Republic of Belarus of Citizens of the Republic of 
Belarus" comes into effect on 1 January 1994. It lifts all 
restrictions on the issuance of a general civil foreign travel 
passport. In order to obtain it, one will not have to produce 
private or service invitations at local visa and registration 
departments. A written application will be sufficient, and a 
passport will be issued in due course. Moreover, there will be 
no need in the new year for a separate permission entry [in the 
passport] stating the country and the time limits for going 
there. The new passport will be valid to go to any country in 
the world a number of times. This was the topic of a news 
conference held in Minsk with the participation of 
representatives of the Foreign Affairs Ministry Consular 
Directorate, the Internal Affairs Ministry Passport and Visa 
Service, and the republic's Border Troops Chief Directorate. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

