<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Inspection Teams Can Arrive Directly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0401201394 Minsk BELAPAN in Russian 1900 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0401201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A point of entry for U.S. military inspection teams 
has been opened at Minsk-2 airport. The teams are coming to 
Belarus to inspect the former USSR bases housing short- and 
medium-range missiles. According to General Major Viktar Vakar, 
head of the National Agency for Control and Inspections, before 
the opening of the facility, U.S. teams arrived via Moscow, 
which contradicted Belarusian sovereignty, as in those cases 
U.S. experts were accompanied by Russian military officials, 
while Belarus had to pay for their airfare. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

