<H3> <TI>   Election Results To Be Handed Over to Parliament </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401155694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1408 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 4 TASS -- The Central Electoral 
Commission will soon hand over to the Federal Assembly (Russian 
Parliament) documentation on the election results to the 
Federation Council (Upper Chamber) and the State Duma (Lower 
Chamber): Final lists of deputies to the two chambers, their 
personal files as well as all financial accounts. This work 
should be completed by the end of the current week, member of 
the Central Electoral Commission andrey Beloborodov told 
ITAR-TASS on Tuesday. 
  He noted that the Central Electoral Commission treats with 
understanding those lawmakers who have not decided whether to be 
members of parliament or to hold their present government posts. 
  "We do not prod legislators, since we understand that there 
will be government reshuffling, and it may turn out that some 
parliamentarians who will give up their seats in parliament, 
will later lose their government jobs," he noted. 
  At the same time Beloborodov stressed that those lawmakers 
who have not decided this question as yet, should remember that 
"the Central Electoral Commission should know for sure who will 
work at the new parliament by the first joint sitting of the two 
chambers which is to be held in the Kremlin next week," he noted. 

</TEXT>

