<H3> <TI>   New Political Bloc Intends To Contest Local Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0501115094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK0501115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report in the "In Brief" column] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- As has become known, shortly before the 
New Year a steering group was formed to set up yet another bloc, 
tentatively called Center. It is expected that the bloc will 
incorporate representatives of all parties and organizations 
which either did not contest the 12 December elections or failed 
to pass one of their stages. The parties affiliated with the 
New Russia bloc are an exception. In particular this bloc will 
apparently include the Russian Social Democratic Center, the 
Russia Revival Union, the SPT, the PT [previous two expansions 
unknown], the Russian Christian Democratic Movement, the 
Democratic Party Moscow branch, and others. The new bloc 
intends to contest elections to local power bodies. 

</TEXT>

