<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Procuracy Chief Reviews Achievements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401224194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401224194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aleksey Kazannik regards the preservation of the 
procuracy system as his main contribution in the post of 
Russia's general procurator. Summing up the results of his work 
in 1993, in an interview to INTERFAX, he stressed that he sees 
in this one of the guarantees for the unity and integrity of 
Russia. Kazannik also said that the General Procuracy has 
dismissed all cases involving charges of economic crimes which 
were instigated for political reasons so as to compromise 
political figures. 
  Touching on his predecessor Valentin Stepankov, the general 
procurator told journalists that on 24 December he signed an 
edict sacking him from the bodies of the procuracy. After his 
resignation, Stepankov was offered various fields of work, 
including the post of trade counsellor at the Russian Embassy in 
Malta. 
  Aleksey Kazannik also said that criminal proceedings on 
charges of corruption are soon to be instituted against Viktor 
Barannikov and Andrey Dunayev. 
  In conclusion Russia's general procurator gave the assurance 
that he will not allow the examination of the case concerning 
the Moscow events of early October 1993 to be spun out over a 
long period. 

</TEXT>

