<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   President's Analytical Center Takes Shape </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0501112094 Moscow KURANTY in Russian 5 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK0501112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [INFORM-KURANTY report: "Brainstorming in the Kremlin"] </F>
  [Text] A certain shakeup in the top spheres of the 
Kremlin's "gray matter" has begun whose aim is allegedly to 
bring together intellectual pro-presidential forces into a 
single fist in the shape of a major analytical center. The 
well-known results of the recent parliamentary elections having 
been noted, a whole company of official presidential advisers -- 
recruited at one time or another more on the nomenklatura basis 
-- were given their marching orders in the Kremlin, and now they 
have started uniting the ranks of presidential experts. 
  Knowledgeable people believe that some analytical structure 
is taking shape within the president's staff. It will be tasked 
with refining the strategic political line, and elaborating a 
course for the future development of which the head of state is 
responsible under the new constitution. The sphere of interests 
of the new super-center will include strategic problems of both 
foreign and domestic policy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

